article_title: Minority, low-income neighborhoods fuel area's healthcare enrollment
article_text:
Minority, low-income neighborhoods fuel area's healthcare enrollment More than 345,000 Houstonians enrolled under federal healthcare plan

Photo: Gary Coronado, Houston Chronicle Majorie Monson, in-person assister with Houston North Enrollment...

The primary enrollees of the federally backed affordable care program in the Houston area continue to be minority and low-income families, based on data from the U.S. Department of Health & Human Services.

article_metadata.author.name: Sarah Kim, John D. Harden, Houston Chronicle
